The Pantheon steering tools

These are the action operators.

1. Reward Rewrite

Change what gets rewarded.

If behavior is bad but rational, don’t moralize first.
Change payoff.

Examples:
	•	reward long-term outcomes, not raw throughput
	•	tie school funding to graduate earnings bands
	•	tie manager comp to durability, not just short-term margin

2. Cost Reinternalization

Force hidden costs back onto the decision-maker.

Examples:
	•	universities absorb part of default risk
	•	platforms bear moderation externalities
	•	firms pay for ecological clean-up

3. Delay Injection

Add friction where harmful speed is the problem.

This matches your transitional geometry doctrine.

Examples:
	•	cooling-off periods
	•	staged approvals
	•	delayed liquidity
	•	escrow releases
	•	reversible probation windows

4. Visibility Correction

Make hidden consequences legible.

Examples:
	•	publish degree ROI by program
	•	show total expected loan cost, not just monthly payment
	•	expose complaint rates, churn, failure modes

5. Exit Restoration

Increase reversibility and bargaining power.

Examples:
	•	refinancing paths
	•	bankruptcy options
	•	portability of credentials
	•	open standards
	•	switching tools

6. Positive-Sum Reframe

Dragonfly move.
Don’t only punish bad actors; redesign the game so cooperation pays more.

Examples:
	•	shared upside contracts
	•	co-ops
	•	aligned subscription models
	•	savings-sharing models
	•	worker/customer ownership layers

