The IAL scoring matrix

Give every system a score from 0–5 on:
	•	Incentive clarity
	•	Proxy distortion
	•	Externality load
	•	Lock-in severity
	•	Exit availability
	•	Timescale coherence
	•	Information symmetry
	•	Positive-sum potential
	•	Ethics stability
	•	Resistance to gaming

Then compute:

Misalignment Index =
Proxy distortion
	•	externality load
	•	lock-in severity
	•	information asymmetry

	•	exit availability
	•	timescale coherence

Not mathematically sacred, but useful.

High score = system likely drifts exploitative unless actively governed.

