The key abstraction

Incentives are really field geometry.

They are invisible slopes in decision space.

People “choose,” but their choices are shaped by:
	•	gradient steepness
	•	friction
	•	visibility
	•	local minima
	•	cliffs
	•	traps
	•	escape ladders

